Core refactor rule
NovaForge’s old data is mostly organized by gameplay category.
Master Repo should keep that strength, but split it through the new hybrid law:

Voxel data = mass, material, structural rules, damage, repair, mining

Modular data = devices, doors, machines, weapons, attachables

Blueprint data = voxel structure + modular attachments

Presentation data = low-poly style, themes, VFX, readability rules

That means the biggest change is:

Old model
ship = mostly stat object

module = stat object

world = location/economy object

New model
ship = voxel hull + room graph + module attachments + stats

station = voxel shell + service modules + economy role

asteroid = voxel material body + ore composition + salvage/mining metadata

derelict = damaged voxel structure + exposed modules + salvage tables

1. Common schema rules
Every major JSON object should share a common base:

{
  "id": "string_id",
  "name": "Human Readable Name",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "tags": ["tag_a", "tag_b"],
  "description": "Optional description"
}
Recommended shared optional fields
{
  "source_archive": "NovaForge",
  "source_file": "data/ships/frigates.json",
  "deprecated": false,
  "notes": "Migration notes here"
}
That gives you provenance and migration safety.

2. Voxel material schema
This is one of the most important new schemas.

Purpose
Defines how structural voxel mass behaves.

File location
data/voxel_materials/*.json
Exact format
{
